.TH "__nfp_net_reconfig" 9 "__nfp_net_reconfig" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__nfp_net_reconfig \- Reconfigure the firmware
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" __nfp_net_reconfig
.BI "(struct nfp_net *nn "  ","
.BI "u32 update "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "nn" 12
NFP Net device to reconfigure
.IP "update" 12
The value for the update field in the BAR config
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Write the update word to the BAR and ping the reconfig queue.  The
poll until the firmware has acknowledged the update by zeroing the
update word.
.SH "RETURN"
Negative errno on error, 0 on success
